00:19:57,112 --> 00:19:59,448
If I expected this...

263
00:19:59,948 --> 00:20:02,492
- I should have killed you then!
-Dad!

264
00:20:02,576 --> 00:20:06,246
Were you thinking of me?
when you ruined my life?

265
00:20:06,330 --> 00:20:08,582
Dong-eun, you need to calm down too.

266
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:10,876
Dad, come in the house.

267
00:20:11,460 --> 00:20:13,295
People are watching. Come on!

268
00:20:13,378 --> 00:20:17,090
Gadura is just lying! Don't listen to her!

269
00:20:25,224 --> 00:20:26,099
Dong-eun.

270
00:20:27,517 --> 00:20:28,602
Tell me.

271
00:20:29,102 --> 00:20:30,354
What's going on?

272
00:20:30,938 --> 00:20:35,067
I came to you before the announcement
on the <i>web</i> page of the Office of Education.

273
00:20:35,150 --> 00:20:36,568
Office of Education?

274
00:20:37,152 --> 00:20:40,113
I know very well that you are innocent.

275
00:20:40,614 --> 00:20:41,698
But...

276
00:20:42,908 --> 00:20:44,826
I was also innocent then.

277
00:20:46,411 --> 00:20:49,248
You're all grown up now, Soo-han. I was...

278
00:20:50,999 --> 00:20:52,751
I was only 16 years old.

279
00:21:03,595 --> 00:21:05,264
You did that?

280
00:21:07,224 --> 00:21:08,642
That's what you did to Mr. Kim?

281
00:21:09,226 --> 00:21:10,936
What exactly are you talking about?

282
00:21:11,728 --> 00:21:12,729
About his death

283
00:21:13,730 --> 00:21:14,898
or his punishment?

284
00:21:15,607 --> 00:21:17,359
Dad!

285
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:19,111
Dad!

286
00:21:19,945 --> 00:21:22,572
Dad!

287
00:21:24,783 --> 00:21:25,993
Dad!

288
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:30,998
Congratulatory bouquets have already started arriving.

289
00:21:34,835 --> 00:21:36,586
I'm going to be a dad too, dad.

290
00:21:38,297 --> 00:21:40,716
A father can do anything for his child.

291
00:21:41,383 --> 00:21:43,468
What's that about...

292
00:21:44,886 --> 00:21:46,555
What are you talking about?

293
00:21:46,638 --> 00:21:48,807
All I have left is an estimate.

294
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:51,935
In a little while, I'll be an inspector.

295
00:21:52,019 --> 00:21:54,396
I will do my best to help you.

296
00:21:56,231 --> 00:21:57,983
I may be retired, but...

297
00:21:58,483 --> 00:22:00,027
Soo-hane, open the window.

298
00:22:00,819 --> 00:22:02,237
Not.

299
00:22:03,071 --> 00:22:04,239
Don't be like that.

300
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:06,992
You know that in our business
rumors spread quickly.

301
00:22:07,075 --> 00:22:10,078
Your reputation becomes rumours,
and rumors about your reputation.

302
00:22:12,998 --> 00:22:14,541
I'm returning your watch.

303
00:22:17,252 --> 00:22:18,253
Good.

304
00:22:18,754 --> 00:22:21,465
Soo-hane, open the window, please.

305
00:22:22,799 --> 00:22:25,052
There is one more thing left...

306
00:22:27,137 --> 00:22:28,638
which you can do.

307
00:22:29,598 --> 00:22:31,183
Remain an exemplary father

308
00:22:31,266 --> 00:22:33,685
who received the Service Award.

309
00:22:34,978 --> 00:22:37,814
Do it for me, please.

310
00:22:40,275 --> 00:22:42,402
Soo-han, please. Window.

311
00:22:49,743 --> 00:22:51,912
Dad!

312
00:22:52,871 --> 00:22:54,456
Dad!

313
00:23:01,338 --> 00:23:03,256
<i>For what happened to Mr. Kim</i>

314
00:23:03,340 --> 00:23:05,384
he himself is to blame, not me.

315
00:23:06,843 --> 00:23:08,720
If you're looking for another culprit,

316
00:23:08,804 --> 00:23:10,889
then it's you, not me.

317
00:23:12,641 --> 00:23:13,642
Fucking bastard!

318
00:23:15,227 --> 00:23:17,145
It's better that way.

319
00:23:17,854 --> 00:23:19,898
I'm glad you stayed the same.

320
00:23:21,775 --> 00:23:22,692
You know what?

321
00:23:23,735 --> 00:23:25,987
Let's move on to what interests you.

322
00:23:27,114 --> 00:23:27,948
Like a mother.

323
00:23:31,243 --> 00:23:35,247
Your daughter Ye-sol is pure and tender-hearted.

324
00:23:36,164 --> 00:23:37,416
He is a good person.

325
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:40,669
She will be your punishment.

326
00:23:40,752 --> 00:23:42,170
I will kill you.

327
00:23:43,422 --> 00:23:46,174
Just try Ye-sol to get a hair off your head,

328
00:23:46,758 --> 00:23:48,009
so you will see.

329
00:23:48,635 --> 00:23:49,803
I'm interested.

330
00:23:50,679 --> 00:23:51,930
What will I see?

331
00:23:52,931 --> 00:23:56,435
You've already broken my body and crushed my soul.

332
00:23:56,935 --> 00:23:58,603
What else can you do for me?

333
00:24:02,566 --> 00:24:05,652
Are you going to transfer her to another school?
Don't even think about it.

334
00:24:06,695 --> 00:24:09,865
Will you move me? Don't even think about it.

335
00:24:10,949 --> 00:24:12,868
You will have to suffer from now on.

336
00:24:13,660 --> 00:24:15,162
As am I.

337
00:24:58,705 --> 00:25:00,165
Fuck it!

338
00:25:29,986 --> 00:25:31,988
<i>How much money do I have to give for condolences?</i>

339
00:25:32,072 --> 00:25:34,157
<i>Damn it, his wife is writing to me again.</i>

340
00:25:34,241 --> 00:25:37,244
<i>For a schoolmate 100,000,</i>
<i>500,000 for a friend</i>

341
00:25:37,327 --> 00:25:39,120
<i>a million won for a pet dog,</i>

342
00:25:39,204 --> 00:25:40,956
<i>and 50,000 for the class teacher.</i>

343
00:25:41,540 --> 00:25:43,583
<i>How much will you give me for the wedding?</i>

344
00:25:44,376 --> 00:25:45,210
<i>A hundred.</i>

345
00:25:45,710 --> 00:25:47,546
<i>My God!</i>

346
00:25:48,463 --> 00:25:49,297
<i>Vona.</i>

347
00:25:52,384 --> 00:25:53,385
Fuck it.

348
00:26:35,302 --> 00:26:38,471
Excuse me, would you mind a moment
holding an umbrella?

349
00:26:39,347 --> 00:26:42,475
I picked up the wine from the secretary.
He's in the passenger seat.

350
00:26:51,359 --> 00:26:53,528
It is sent by Mr. Shin from Hanjinmaru.

351
00:26:55,614 --> 00:26:56,615
You drink it.

352
00:26:56,698 --> 00:26:59,451
If it's from Mr. Shin, it's worth a million won.

353
00:26:59,534 --> 00:27:00,368
Please?

354
00:27:01,119 --> 00:27:03,121
I can't, sir.

355
00:27:06,958 --> 00:27:08,585
My hands are full.

356
00:27:10,462 --> 00:27:12,380
I can't take something that expensive.

357
00:27:13,214 --> 00:27:16,468
I wouldn't even know how to drink it, sir.
It's okay.

358
00:27:16,551 --> 00:27:20,221
I speak when something is right.
And I've said it before.

359
00:27:21,348 --> 00:27:22,932
I don't know what the problem is.

360
00:27:23,767 --> 00:27:24,976
Sir?

361
00:27:25,060 --> 00:27:28,647
Then buy a 10,000 won wine
on the way home.

362
00:27:28,730 --> 00:27:29,981
And some cheese.

363
00:27:30,732 --> 00:27:34,194
First drink the 10,000 won wine,
and then this.

364
00:27:35,654 --> 00:27:38,490
That's how you'll learn how to drink it.
See you tomorrow.

365
00:28:08,687 --> 00:28:10,730
<i>You know what I once wanted?</i>

366
00:28:13,608 --> 00:28:14,943
Dad!

367
00:28:16,569 --> 00:28:19,906
Dad's vitamin! Daddy's darling!

368
00:28:22,909 --> 00:28:24,577
<i>I wanted to one day</i>

369
00:28:24,661 --> 00:28:28,540
<i>I forget your name and your face.</i>

370
00:28:30,208 --> 00:28:33,044
<i>If I met you somewhere, I would wonder...</i>

371
00:28:35,380 --> 00:28:36,506
<i>who are you.</i>

372
00:28:37,632 --> 00:28:40,969
<i>I hoped I wouldn't remember you anymore.</i>

373
00:28:44,389 --> 00:28:47,392
<i>If you think about it, it's horrible.</i>

374
00:28:48,643 --> 00:28:51,229
<i>My life revolves around you.</i>

375
00:28:53,773 --> 00:28:55,942
<i>And because of that fact</i>

376
00:28:57,318 --> 00:29:01,823
<i>the world your daughter lives in</i>
<i>it will revolve around me.</i>

377
00:29:04,409 --> 00:29:07,620
<i>I will take responsibility</i>
<i>for her resentment.</i>

378
00:29:08,496 --> 00:29:09,956
<i>That is the price of revenge.</i>

379
00:29:16,629 --> 00:29:20,800
FOR YEON-JIN

380
00:29:35,732 --> 00:29:37,901
What was it? Who did it?

381
00:29:43,031 --> 00:29:45,200
I received a photo,

382
00:29:47,118 --> 00:29:49,788
as well as a photo of Soo-hee.

383
00:29:50,622 --> 00:29:52,040
Thank you, ma'am.

384
00:29:52,123 --> 00:29:53,958
I had to do it.

385
00:29:55,543 --> 00:29:57,295
I was young then.

386
00:29:58,797 --> 00:30:00,882
You were close with So-hee?

387
00:30:05,345 --> 00:30:07,889
Pads, please. The ones with wings.

388
00:30:07,972 --> 00:30:09,057
Just a moment.

389
00:30:16,648 --> 00:30:19,234
These are hydrogen peroxide
and ointment for burns.

390
00:30:19,317 --> 00:30:20,401
4700 won please.

391
00:30:27,408 --> 00:30:28,243
<i>I didn't.</i>

392
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:30,703
<i>When she was mistreated,</i>

393
00:30:32,038 --> 00:30:32,872
<i>I was</i>

394
00:30:34,833 --> 00:30:36,376
just an observer.

395
00:30:37,335 --> 00:30:39,420
And then I became a victim.

396
00:30:42,423 --> 00:30:43,758
And now...

397
00:30:45,343 --> 00:30:47,136
Now I will be the perpetrator.

398
00:30:48,471 --> 00:30:52,392
it's late
but I will no longer be just an observer.

399
00:30:53,768 --> 00:30:54,769
In other words,

400
00:30:56,396 --> 00:30:58,565
Is this the start of a great battle?

401
00:30:59,691 --> 00:31:00,525
That's right.

402
00:31:02,277 --> 00:31:04,612
I can tell you only one thing.

403
00:31:06,155 --> 00:31:07,240
Win.

404
00:31:08,950 --> 00:31:13,371
For 16-year-old Dong-eun
and for 36-year-old Dong-eun.

405
00:31:14,205 --> 00:31:15,498
I'm rooting for you.

406
00:31:19,294 --> 00:31:20,128
Good.

407
00:31:22,046 --> 00:31:22,881
I…

408
00:31:24,465 --> 00:31:25,967
I'll do my best.

409
00:31:37,645 --> 00:31:40,732
There you are. I was afraid you wouldn't come.

410
00:31:41,399 --> 00:31:42,567
Why wouldn't I?

411
00:31:43,276 --> 00:31:44,193
You met them.

412
00:31:44,277 --> 00:31:47,030
And you didn't tell them that we met.

413
00:31:47,113 --> 00:31:48,615
Why would I tell them?

414
00:31:49,657 --> 00:31:52,660
I invested everything I have in you.
I'm going all the way.

415
00:31:55,038 --> 00:31:55,872
Remember one thing.

416
00:31:58,708 --> 00:32:01,210
You're dead if you get me into some shit.

417
00:32:07,926 --> 00:32:08,843
have you eaten

418
00:32:13,514 --> 00:32:14,682
I'll cut the story short.

419
00:32:14,766 --> 00:32:17,018
Let it last. We'll talk over food.

420
00:32:17,685 --> 00:32:18,519
What do you like?

421
00:32:27,695 --> 00:32:28,529
Sorry!

422
00:32:29,364 --> 00:32:30,698
A bottle of soju, please.

423
00:32:35,078 --> 00:32:36,162
Why don't you eat?

424
00:32:36,871 --> 00:32:39,624
I already ate.
What about what I asked for?

425
00:32:53,429 --> 00:32:54,263
Do you want a drink?

426
00:32:54,347 --> 00:32:55,723
I already drank it.

427
00:33:05,566 --> 00:33:06,985
Information about Sarah's drug

428
00:33:07,485 --> 00:33:09,821
and about the guy Hye-jeong is obsessed with.

429
00:33:13,324 --> 00:33:14,909
And the hairs I gave you?

430
00:33:15,785 --> 00:33:16,953
They match.

431
00:33:20,581 --> 00:33:23,251
Seriously? Jae-jun has a child?

432
00:33:23,751 --> 00:33:26,087
- Where is he?
- I will play that card.

433
00:33:27,672 --> 00:33:28,673
Take this.

434
00:33:32,593 --> 00:33:35,680
Morgue? What's there?

435
00:33:36,848 --> 00:33:40,018
- Is this a better card?
- Yes, if you want money.

436
00:33:40,518 --> 00:33:43,104
You will see for yourself who is there.

437
00:33:47,108 --> 00:33:49,027
I will make money from this.

438
00:33:50,028 --> 00:33:50,862
Isn't it?

439
00:34:01,873 --> 00:34:03,541
D-3. It's here.

440
00:34:10,548 --> 00:34:12,383
YOON SO-HEE
ARRIVED 15. 12. 2004.

441
00:34:15,136 --> 00:34:15,970
So,

442
00:34:17,555 --> 00:34:19,474
Yoon So-hee lies here

443
00:34:19,974 --> 00:34:21,142
more than a decade?

444
00:34:21,225 --> 00:34:22,226
That's right.

445
00:34:22,310 --> 00:34:24,479
The bill is over 100 million won.

446
00:34:24,979 --> 00:34:28,649
The police concluded that she had killed herself.
Parents did not believe.

447
00:34:29,317 --> 00:34:31,319
They don't contact us.

448
00:34:31,819 --> 00:34:35,406
We can't remove the body
without the consent of the family.

449
00:34:36,240 --> 00:34:37,241
May I…

450
00:34:40,286 --> 00:34:43,206
May I see her? That is, a corpse?

451
00:34:43,289 --> 00:34:44,791
I don't think I should…

452
00:34:45,875 --> 00:34:48,628
- You are not a family member?
- I didn't.

453
00:34:49,212 --> 00:34:52,548
We are friends. We know each other from high school.

454
00:34:53,132 --> 00:34:55,635
You must be accompanied by a family member.

455
00:34:55,718 --> 00:34:57,637
It's a problem for us too.

456
00:34:57,720 --> 00:35:01,307
Try to convince someone from the family.

457
00:35:01,849 --> 00:35:05,186
It's fine if they don't want to claim the body.

458
00:35:08,815 --> 00:35:10,483
<i>You want to know what I want?</i>

459
00:35:12,944 --> 00:35:16,531
<i>Do I want Myeong-o's wings</i>
<i>cause a hurricane?</i>

460
00:35:18,533 --> 00:35:22,120
<i>Myeong-o has no wings, Yeon-jin.</i>

461
00:35:28,709 --> 00:35:32,964
<i>He doesn't deserve to have something so beautiful.</i>

462
00:35:39,804 --> 00:35:41,889
<i>Myeong-o is my SD card.</i>

463
00:35:42,390 --> 00:35:45,601
<i>I'll put it in the camera</i>
<i>and record whatever I want.</i>

464
00:35:47,562 --> 00:35:49,230
That will be worth a lot of money.

465
00:35:51,482 --> 00:35:54,986
Dong-eun, you've become an interesting curmudgeon.

466
00:36:07,790 --> 00:36:13,004
ROOM 701
PATIENT: YOON JEONG-HWAN

467
00:36:20,636 --> 00:36:22,638
Where is 701's Yoon Jeong-hwan?

468
00:36:23,514 --> 00:36:27,518
Didn't you hear? He went into shock this morning.

469
00:37:00,718 --> 00:37:01,844
are you ok

470
00:37:02,428 --> 00:37:03,346
Isn't she hot?

471
00:37:08,267 --> 00:37:09,268
I'm fine.

472
00:37:39,257 --> 00:37:42,134
Ye-sol, did anyone bully you at school?

473
00:37:42,218 --> 00:37:44,470
- Did anyone hit you?
- What is it, mom?

474
00:37:44,553 --> 00:37:48,057
If your teacher does something to punish you,
that's not right.

475
00:37:48,140 --> 00:37:50,893
Has anyone put it on you?
something hot on the body?

476
00:37:50,977 --> 00:37:52,979
Why would anyone do that?

477
00:37:53,062 --> 00:37:54,480
That's mean.

478
00:37:54,563 --> 00:37:56,440
They should be scolded.

479
00:37:57,775 --> 00:38:00,778
I will play <i>Among Us</i> with my friends.

480
00:38:04,740 --> 00:38:05,866
Ye-sol!

481
00:38:15,835 --> 00:38:18,212
<i>He always comes on Fridays.</i>

482
00:38:18,796 --> 00:38:21,632
<i>Three out of five photos I take</i>
<i>they are sharpened.</i>

483
00:38:29,640 --> 00:38:32,101
GO CLUB PAGODA

484
00:40:12,410 --> 00:40:15,746
<i>I learned it very quickly, Yeon-jin.</i>

485
00:40:16,997 --> 00:40:18,666
<i>I had a clear purpose.</i>

486
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:23,671
<i>You win if you win houses</i>
<i>that your opponent built.</i>

487
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:27,091
<i>It's beautiful.</i>

488
00:40:38,394 --> 00:40:39,687
You were gone for a long time.

489
00:40:40,563 --> 00:40:42,440
Yes, I had to work.

490
00:40:44,567 --> 00:40:45,734
What do you do?

491
00:40:46,694 --> 00:40:50,197
I fooled the naive and made them cry.

492
00:40:51,991 --> 00:40:53,284
Are you making good money?

493
00:40:54,034 --> 00:40:55,161
And not really.

494
00:40:55,995 --> 00:40:57,163
I'm a good person.

495
00:41:03,002 --> 00:41:04,545
Where did you learn to play?

496
00:41:06,172 --> 00:41:07,256
In the park.

497
00:41:09,550 --> 00:41:11,635
Your answers are unexpected.

498
00:41:36,076 --> 00:41:37,411
For 20,000 per lot?

499
00:41:47,213 --> 00:41:48,047
Last move.

500
00:41:49,715 --> 00:41:51,091
There is no going back.

501
00:41:53,135 --> 00:41:54,678
Will you pay in cash?

502
00:41:56,180 --> 00:41:57,014
What?

503
00:42:06,106 --> 00:42:07,358
It was fun.

504
00:42:10,611 --> 00:42:11,946
Let's play for 50,000.

505
00:42:14,073 --> 00:42:15,241
Another party?

506
00:42:18,619 --> 00:42:19,870
<i>Yeon-jin,</i>

507
00:42:20,621 --> 00:42:24,875
<i>you want me to tell you the real reason</i>
<i>why do I love him?</i>

508
00:42:27,545 --> 00:42:28,796
That would be gambling.

509
00:42:30,965 --> 00:42:31,882
Is it?

510
00:42:32,466 --> 00:42:36,512
<i>When you play go,</i>
<i>in silence you show what you long for.</i>

511
00:42:36,595 --> 00:42:41,225
<i>You quarrel and you are misled.</i>
<i>The opponent and you expose each other.</i>

512
00:42:43,060 --> 00:42:44,853
<i>Maybe your opponent doesn't fight back.</i>

513
00:42:48,232 --> 00:42:49,066
<i>In that case…</i>

514
00:42:51,569 --> 00:42:53,070
<i>it's just a game of goa.</i>

515
00:42:54,488 --> 00:42:57,157
I want that. Gamble.

516
00:44:54,441 --> 00:44:59,446
Subtitle translation: Davor Fröbe


